\begin_layout Subsection
Aspect in DEM
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Aspect identifies the down slope direction of the maximum rate of change
 in value from each cell to its neighbors.
 Aspect can be thought of as the slope direction.
 The values of the output raster will be the compass direction of the aspect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A moving 3 x 3 window visits each cell in the input raster and for each
 cell in the center of the window, an aspect value is calculated using an
 algorithm that incorporates the values of the cell's eight neighbors.
 The cells are identified as letters 'a' to 'i', with 'e' representing the
 cell for which the aspect is being calculated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The rate of change in the x direction for cell 'e' is calculated with the
 following algorithm:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[dz/dx=((c+2f+i)-(a+2d+g)/(8*x_{cellsize})]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The rate of change in the y direction for cell 'e' is calculated with the
 following algorithm:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[dz/dy=((g+2h+i)-(a+2b+c)/(8*y_{cellsize})]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Taking the rate of change in both the x and y direction for cell 'e', aspect
 is calculated using: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[aspect=57.29578*atan([dz/dy],-[dz/dx])]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The aspect value is then converted to compass direction values (0–360 degrees),
 according to the following rule: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset space \quad{}
\end_inset

if aspect < 0 
\end_layout

