\begin_layout Subsection
Decision tree
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A decision tree is a decision support tool that uses a tree-like graph or
 model of decisions and their possible consequences.
 We create a decision tree from the input training data.
 The training data contains a DEM, land-cover class classification and river
 presence and absence information.
 From River presence and absence algorithm we get the river distance matrix.
 The leaf nodes in decision tree represent the land-cover class.
 We query in decision tree just like a binary search tree.
 We use this decision tree to assign land-cover class values to synthetic
 landscape which in turn is used to assign suitability values to each and
 every pixel.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename 14.png
	scale 80

